<div id="bookReviews">
  




  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section firstReview">
      

<div id="review_474939026" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/474939026" />
    <a title="Mar" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15371465-mar"><img alt="Mar" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1483047354p2/15371465.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/474939026?book_show_action=true">Dec 10, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mar" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mar" href="/user/show/15371465-mar">Mar</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780345805072" href="/book/show/16280058-manuscrito-encontrado-en-accra">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer474939026" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer875492718303903672">When I first picked up the book, I compared it to Khalil Gibran&apos;s &quot;The Profit&quot;. I was a bit disillusioned, and stopped reading for a bit. Having some time one day, I picked up the book again with the hope that I would finish it quickly and move on to the next read. How mistaken I was! The 3 chapters I read that day were directly addressing issues I was experiencing at the time!<br/><br/>This book is definitely one you want to read slowly, ponder on the messages and hopefully apply to your life. Its a book</span>
  <span id="freeText875492718303903672" style="display:none">When I first picked up the book, I compared it to Khalil Gibran's "The Profit". I was a bit disillusioned, and stopped reading for a bit. Having some time one day, I picked up the book again with the hope that I would finish it quickly and move on to the next read. How mistaken I was! The 3 chapters I read that day were directly addressing issues I was experiencing at the time!<br /><br />This book is definitely one you want to read slowly, ponder on the messages and hopefully apply to your life. Its a book you want to keep in your personal library and refer back to it.<br /><br /><br />Paolo Coelho did not disillusion. </span>
  <a data-text-id="875492718303903672" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


