              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8665620192329074856">Read by Jeremy Irons, Paulo Coelho&apos;s book, Manuscript Found in Accra (pronounced a CRA) is more than a book. It is a contemplation on human values that have endured the passage of time.<br/><br/>The story is told through the eyes of the Copt. It is 1099 in Jerusalem and the Crusaders are at the gate. The Copt has summoned the townspeople to address their fears. He talks of many things: defeat, struggle, the nature of the enemy; they contemplate the will to change and the virtues of loyalty and solitude; t</span>
  <span id="freeText8665620192329074856" style="display:none">Read by Jeremy Irons, Paulo Coelho's book, Manuscript Found in Accra (pronounced a CRA) is more than a book. It is a contemplation on human values that have endured the passage of time.<br /><br />The story is told through the eyes of the Copt. It is 1099 in Jerusalem and the Crusaders are at the gate. The Copt has summoned the townspeople to address their fears. He talks of many things: defeat, struggle, the nature of the enemy; they contemplate the will to change and the virtues of loyalty and solitude; they ultimately turn to questions about beauty, love, wisdom, sex, elegance and what the future holds.<br /><br />This is a book well worthy of a re-read (or in this case a listen followed by a read!!). On the second go-around, I will take each subject and provide one quote.<br /><br />To get us started, I will include one in this preliminary review.<br /><br />DEFEAT. Only he who gives up is defeated.<br /><br />4 stars</span>
  <a data-text-id="8665620192329074856" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
