  <span id="freeText13389994071645182646" style="display:none">When I first found out about the book from my friend, when she posted a quotation from the book, i really got interested in reading it. The words was full of wisdom, that's why i was really attracted into it. I got a copy of the book last two days ago. And to my amazement, i only read it for just almost two hours! <br />This one is really a page turner. Every word and every detail brought so much knowledge and realizations over me. The main character which is the-so-called "Copt" serves as the source of a vast of wisdom, which is based merely on his experiences and personal search for meaning in this life. <br />While i was reading it, i felt like i was reading the book of Ecclesiastes in the Old Testament of the Bible. It has a vast view of the world we live in, and the experiences we come across in our daily life. The Copt is like a 'Preacher', who is very wise and has a deeper understanding of human nature. <br />Thumbs up to Paulo Coelho for making such wonderful books that inspires generations all over the world!</span>
